Sentencas: A new perovskite cathode, Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-delta, performs well for oxygen-reduction reactions in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Insight into the Structure and Functional Application of the Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: We gain insight into the crystal structure of Sr1-xCexCoO3-delta (x = 0.05, 0.1) and temperature-dependent structural evolution of Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-d by X-ray diffraction, neutron powder diffraction, and scanning transmission electron microscopy experiments.
Titulo: Insight into the Structure and Functional Application of the Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Sr0.9Ce0.1CoO3-delta shows a perfectly cubic structure (a = a0), with a large oxygen deficiency in a single oxygen site; however, Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-delta exhibits a tetragonal perovskite superstructure with a double c axis, defined in the P4/mmm space group, that contains two crystallographically different cobalt positions, with distinct oxygen environments.
Titulo: Insight into the Structure and Functional Application of the Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The structural evolution of Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-delta at high temperatures was further studied by in situ temperature-dependent NPD experiments.
Titulo: Insight into the Structure and Functional Application of the Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: At 1100 K, the oxygen atoms in Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-delta show large and highly anisotropic displacement factors, suggesting a significant ionic mobility.
Titulo: Insight into the Structure and Functional Application of the Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The test cell with a La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.83Mg0.17O3-delta-electrolyte-supported (similar to 300 mu m thickness) configuration yields peak power densities of 0.25 and 0.48 W cm(-2) at temperatures of 1023 and 1073 K, respectively, with pure H-2 as the fuel and ambient air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Insight into the Structure and Functional Application of the Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical impedance spectra evolution with time of the symmetric cathode fuel cell measured at 1073 K shows that the Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-delta cathode possesses superior ORR catalytic activity and long-term stability.
Titulo: Insight into the Structure and Functional Application of the Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Mixed ionic-electronic conduction properties of Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-delta account for its good performance as an oxygen-reduction catalyst.
Titulo: Insight into the Structure and Functional Application of the Sr0.95Ce0.05CoO3-δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
